# argus DB-backup signature VERIFY key — Ed25519 public key (PEM). NON-SECRET, committed on purpose:
# pinning it in git makes it tamper-evident and means restore reads the verify key from the repo, never from
# the same bucket an attacker could write. The matching PRIVATE key lives ONLY in Key Vault
# (argus-backup-signing-key) and on the backup host's tmpfs at sign time — never here.
#
# Populated 2026-06-22 from the Key Vault signing key (one-time, after populate-keyvault.sh), via:
#   az keyvault secret show --vault-name <vault> --name argus-backup-signing-key --query value -o tsv \
#     | openssl pkey -pubout            # use real OpenSSL 3 (macOS LibreSSL cannot)
# To rotate, see infra/backup/README.md §"Backup signing key" (coordinated keyring — keep the old block
# until no live backup is signed by the old key) and docs/threat-models/db-backup.md.
-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----
MCowBQYDK2VwAyEAWtCD5GGXUGIUC96WxYLEqt5oVBI18GK2O94U0v+twgA=
-----END PUBLIC KEY-----
